# CHANGELOG.md and NEWS.md

After completing substantive work in a session, update the root logs **before ending the turn**.

Skip only for pure Q&A, exploration with no edits, or when the user explicitly says not to log.

## CHANGELOG.md (commits / PRs)

- Append under `## [Unreleased]` (newest dated entries at the top of that section).
- Do **not** put unfinished work under a released version heading.
- Release sections use git tags: `## [X.Y.Z]` matches tag `vX.Y.Z`.
- When a release tag is cut (or the user prepares a release), move applicable `[Unreleased]` items into `## [X.Y.Z] - YYYY-MM-DD` and leave `[Unreleased]` for ongoing work.
- Preserve older tag sections unless asked to rewrite them.

Session entry format under `[Unreleased]`:

```markdown
### YYYY-MM-DD — short title

- **Why:** user intent / problem being solved
- **What:** concise bullets of what changed (areas/files, behavior)
```

Use this log when drafting commit messages and PR summaries.

## NEWS.md (startup modal)

- Source for the welcome/startup modal “Latest News” list (`src/lib/news/`).
- Same tag sections as the changelog: `[Unreleased]` then `## [X.Y.Z]` (newest first).
- Bullets are **short, user-facing** product highlights — not internal commit/PR notes.
- When a user-visible feature ships in a session, add a bullet under `[Unreleased]` (or update an existing one). Skip pure refactors, tests-only, or infra unless the user would care on startup.
- Keep each version section short (a few bullets); the modal shows the newest ~3 non-empty sections.
- On release tag: move/promote `[Unreleased]` news into `## [X.Y.Z]`.
